                    "company": "SLB",
                    "description": "Directional drilling and measurements while drilling.\n\n  - Operating a large number of tools while they were used to create, or being integrated into the bottom hole assembly during drilling or logging operations;\n  - Drilling wells according to drilling program given by the client, following the desired well trajectory, delivering drilling mechanics and formation evaluation data achieved with the MWD and LWD tools in real time or recorded mode to the client;\n  - Maintaining a good signal from MWD tool, having various and continuous information about the drilling environment into the wellbore, monitoring the drilling process accurately and identifying any potential hazards related to well control and drilling string integrity;\n  - Prepairing fishing diagrams, programming and testing the tools on rig site prior to running into hole;\n  - Assisting the drilling crew while the BHA was picked up on rig floor by communicating the correct values for make up torque, making sure that the tools are lifted safely and in a correct manner, performed nuclear source transfers;\n  - Held pre-job meetings and communicate clearly the procedure to OIM, client representative and drilling crew prior nuclear jobs related to nuclear source transfers;\n  - Keeping and accurate record of all the M/LWD tools, nuclear sources, batteries containers, dumb iron components, handling tools and unit equipment on rig site;\n  - Formation evaluation Logs and real time chart interpretation;\n  - Creating backload papers and dangerous goods for all the equipment sent to the base or other rigs, securing the loads inside offshore containers or baskets, creating reports on a daily basis regarding timings, drilling parameters and presenting current state of the tools while drilling or logging;\n  - Being a part of Schlumberger a very strong culture related to QHSE was shared to us and we were encouraged to create daily reports about near misses, accidents or hazards encountered on rig site.",
